homedescription: Sound and Mountain Views from this custom, private, NW Contemporary home in Seahurst. Vaulted ceilings, wood beams; this home offers walls of windows with sunny views to the west as well as to the forest setting with trails to the east. Master on the main. Three additional bedrooms plus an office with built-ins. Heated bathroom floors, gas fireplaces, large family room and lots of storage. Workshop adjacent to carport. Easy commute to Seattle.
whatownerloves:
On one side of the house is a wall of windows and views of the Sound and gorgeous sunsets. On the other side is a wall of windows that over look your own private forest with trails. The space is very bright and light, with lots of beautiful wood; it's almost like living in a tree house. Multiple decks allow for different viewing points; fireworks over the Sound from the front deck on the 4th, bird watching and BBQing on the side deck and morning coffee on your private balcony. The house was custom designed and built for the previous owners and there are a lot of very cool built ins; including a loft with a ladder in one of the kid's rooms! Lots of sun in the front yard makes it easy to grow vegetables, herbs and flowers. 

The neighborhood is very quiet and peaceful and there is an annual block party in the summer. You are in walking distance to coffee and tea shops, a great Italian restaurant, beauty salons, a bus stop with express access to Seattle, a convenience store, a consignment store and the post office. You are a ten minute drive to Olde Town Burien and all it's amenities; including the Tin Room Theatre, Amore Bakery (great chocolate croissants), and the Thursday farmer's market and monthly art walk. Commuting to Seattle or the airport is a breeze with rarely any traffic and the new drive thru Starbucks makes it's easy to get your caffeine fix on your way to work.

This home was professionally appraised as part of a refinancing in September of 2014 at $296,000 with a positive value projection. This places the value of this home at the very top of its location and leading the market when compared to homes similar in size, age and accommodations in the "98166" zip code. A rare gem in a great location. This home uniquely balances security and privacy with accessibility to community with its locations being near Burien's downtown neighborhood, shopping, and I-518 which leads to South Center, SeaTac International Airport and Bellevue, and I-509 which leads directly to the west side of Seattle and connects with neighborhoods such as Fremont and Ballard. 

Neighborhood Description

This home is located on a well maintained but less used street. Within one block is the City of Burien's Community Center, a community garden, Dottie Harper Park, and a skate park/sports field. The street is the boarder between the neighborhood of Chelsea Park, a community of winding streets and postwar homes full of longtime residents and new homeowners, and the neighborhood of Dottie Harper Park, an area that has historically been the home of a number of community events such as Burien's Wild Strawberry Festival, sporting events, art shows, the Burien Actors Theatre, Burien's Arts-a-Glow Lantern Festival, the B-Town Brewfest, as well as many other events and has recently been proposed as Burien's new Arts and Cultural district. 

There are a number of schools, stores, gas stations, restaurants, and coffee shops within one mile of the home including Burien's Town Square neighborhood which is home to a number of local and independent businesses, Burien City Hall, Burien's largest library, and Burien Town Square Park.

The home is also located within walking distance to a number of bus routes and the Burien Park and Ride which is the area's main transit center for buses into Seattle, Bellevue, and Tacoma.

homedescription: This home is designed for maximum flexibility.  It is definitely more than meets the eye.   A Bed and Breakfast with private owners quarters on the top two floors?  A perfect place for someone who would like their guests and tenants to pay their mortgage for them.  It also boasts of recycled material throughout.  Maple floors from a basketball court.  Cedar siding salvaged from an Issaquah home.  Galvanized siding salvaged from a 100 year old Marysville barn.  The views are great on every floor, but the third floor deck area view is the piece de resistance, with a 230 degree view from Capital Hill to Crown Hill.  Currently the 2nd and 3rd floors are framed with rough-in electrical and plumbing, so you can select your own finishes for your personal 1500 sf "apartment".  The first floor has been successfully rented on Airbnb for $180 per night and the basement MIL apartment has always had excellent tenants who appreciate living near, but not in downtown Fremont.  This house can earn 50K+ per year and provide you with an amazing place to live.  The price reflects the earning potential.
whatownerloves: The location, views, and flexible nature of this home are it's best assets.  Live on one floor or all three, depending on your needs.

homedescription: Charming mid-century townhome completely renovated in 2008. As you enter the paved patio area you will be greeted with beautiful mature gardens.  You'll  envision yourself having coffee in the garden and afternoon bbq's. As you proceed into residence you'll be impressed with modern Ann Sacks glass tiled kitchen and stainless appliances.The living room, with large double-pane windows, sits looking west toward the Ballard bridge with views of the Ballard waterway, the Ballard Locks and The Olympic Mountains. Two bedrooms and one bath downstairs with a private fenced west facing back yard. Oak hardwood floors throughout. Great condo alternative - No dues! Walking distance to many restaurants such as Bones & Bourbon, Frelard Pizza, Drunky's Two Shoe BBQ, Tray, Giddy Up Burgers, Uneeda Burger, Paseo's Caribbean Restaurant, Roux, and LightHouse Roasters.   If breweries are on your list Hale's Ales, Fremont Brewing, Bad Jimmys Brewing Co., Maritime Brewery and Stoup Brewing to mention a few are close by. Multiple grocery  stores are within close proximity such as Ballard Market, Trader Joes, Marketime Foods and Fred Meyers.  Attractions within walking distance include the Seattle Zoo, The Fremont Solstice Parade and Fair and central Fremont shops. We are centrally located to the U-District, Downtown and adjacent neighborhoods such as Ballard, Queen Anne, Magnolia, Greenlake, PhinneyRidge, Wallingford and Westlake.  There is easy access to the 99 without long waits as we sit only 9 blocks west of the access point.  The Ballard bridge is easily accessed sitting approximately 12 blocks west of our location.  This residence is perfect for the person who values being able to walk to a multitude of establishments. It is also perfect if you have to commute.  After all, Fremont is the "Center of the Universe".
whatownerloves: Not only does the proximity to local establishments and price point make this property a great choice but so do the lovely gardens.  Its a little retreat in the midst of the city.

homedescription: New construction house in the heart of Ballard. Great open floor plan with large master bedroom loft. Vaulted ceilings with tons of light, modern styling and finishes. The short walk to "all things Ballard" is awesome. I leave the car at home all weekend. It is also close to local parks and even though it's blocks from Market Street, the neighborhood is incredibly quiet. I've also had a 400 square foot outdoor patio professionally tiled with 2'x'2' concrete tiles. It's like an extra large room outdoors. Perfect for summer parties. There's no up-keep, just clean the house and go! Also this is a HOUSE, not a townhouse or condo. No dues, you own the property as well.

Wander throughout and experience the warmth of the English Tudor style with its rich woodwork. See and literally feel the quality. Then go out onto the deck and immerse yourself in the absolute privacy with not another house in sight. Enjoy your 165 foot border along the forested greenbelt leading into Salmon Creek Ravine Park. Close your eyes for a while and listen to the total absence of noise. All of this and only 15 minutes from Downtown Seattle.

Downstairs bathroom has a full bath and would make a great bedroom, awesome office or just a great place to sleep during the two weeks it's hot in Seattle.  This townhome also has a 2 car garage (YES! - Two Car!) making parking on Capitol Hill a non-issue.  Walk out the front door to the park and to 15th Ave and all the restaurants, coffee shops, bakeries, supermarkets, etc.  If you don't feel like going out, the front yard is fenced, and great for dogs and BBQs.  No more walking your dog at 6AM in the rain.....just let the pups out the front door.  It's extremely secure.  Walk to buses to get you to South Lake Union, downtown, Int'l District, or the eastside.  Or just walk to downtown in 20 minutes.  If you consider the size (3 bed/3.5 bath), the parking (2 garage bays within your unit), the location (on 15th - 3 blocks to Coastal Kitchen, 2 blocks to Pike/Pine, 4 short blocks to 19th, downtown, etc.), and the yard (unique ability to be in the park, but behind your fenced in yard), then this is about as good as it gets.

Neighborhood Description  Zoned L3.  

This is a historical neighborhood among mansions of early Seattle.
Just blocks from the famous Volunteer Park and all  Broadway has to offer.





 Welcome to A unique Oasis in the City of Seattle on Capitol Hill. It was built in 1929, Rooms are oversized with hardwood floors dressed up with oriental carpets. The original Spa like bathroom has leaded glass arched windows overlooking lush majestic palm trees. Very European, with all original tile, spa tub for your relaxation.



 In your spacious lounge, living area you have a brand new leather sofa where you can read, relax or watch television.



 You can set at your dining table with your Seattle's Famous Coffee, or sip a glass of local wine while working on your lap top or just trying to decide what you want to do. So much to do, So little time...... There are large windows that let in more than ample sunlight.



 If you don't wish to dine out in one of the many great restaurants, many in close walking distance, you can prepare your meal in your very own European inspired kitchen. There you will find everything you need but the food.



 The bedroom is very cozy and there is plenty of closet area.



 If you don't have all you need, let us know so we can work on getting it for you.
 JUST BLOCKS FROM MAJOR HOSPITALS.

 JUST 2 Blocks from the Famous Beautiful Volunteer Park, Conservatory. Asian Art Museum, Cal Anderson Park. This Beautiful Home is Located in the Heartbeat of Seattle's CAPITOL HILL. In walk able distance is: Downtown Seattle, the Convention Center, PIKE STREET MARKET, SEATTLE AQUARIUM, SEATTLE ART MUSEUM, WATERFRONT SHOPS, ANTIQUE STORES, SEATTLE CENTER, SPACE NEEDLE. Within a 5 Minute Drive You Will Find, The University of Washington, Woodland Park Zoo, Boeing Field, The Flight Museum, Ferries to the Olympic Peninsula, The Ballard Lox, Mariners and Seahawks Stadium, Pacific Galleries Antique Mall, West Seattle and Alki Beach. Only 15 min. Drive to the Seatac International Airport, Bellevue and Redmond. One Block From Major Bus Line. More near by Places- Washington State Convention Center/ trade Center, Paramount Theater, Pacific Center and Westlake Center...........FOR MORE INFO AND PICTURES......... website www.villaststefan.com

New roof & energy efficient windows, wood floors, modern kitchen and in-unit washer/dryer are just few of the great things about this unit.  2013 remodel added a large bookshelf and converted a closet space into a work area.  Unit also features one-of-a-kind exclusive access to the roof which has stunning straight ahead views of the Space Needle, The Sound and The Olympics.  Plans are in place to rebuild a small deck on the roof in the summer of 2015 - room enough for four people to enjoy a lovely outdoor summer dinner.  Unit is 1/2 from excellent coffee shop (Analog) and a quick walk to QFC on Broadway as well as numerous bars and restaurants on Olive Way and Summit Ave.  Quick access to I-5 is a bonus as well as downtown being an easy walk away - about 20 mins to Pike Place Market.
whatownerloves: Loft area offers fantastic southern exposure into unit, while its' location in the building (NE Corner) means it is insulated from street noise.  Exclusive roof top access is a huge bonus with many dinners/drinks have been enjoyed on it while soaking in the view of the mountains and the Space Needle.  I also love the well maintained wood floors and the character associated with a building built in 1914.  Being 1/2 a block from Analog Coffee and a quick walk to the bars and restaurants on Olive Way is great, also nice is being a quick walk away from the nice QFC on Broadway.  So many options for dining and drinking make this an ideal location while being buffered from the noise and chaos of said activities if you desire it.

homedescription:
New driveway and newly added RV parking in the back yard!

Welcome home to this beautiful 3200+ square foot Issaquah property! This 4 BR home boasts large open living spaces, over-sized bedrooms, remodeled baths & windows galore allowing an for an abundance of natural light. Fireplaces in both the living room and family room. Updated kitchen w/granite counters,double ovens & mountain views. Two car garage and huge fully fenced yard. New 30 yr roof,int paint & carpet.Close to Downtown Issaquah shops & restaurants

Neighborhood Description

Close to dowtown Issaquah, restaurants, theaters, Historic Gilman Village, salmon hatchery.  Convenient I-90 access for easy commute to Bellevue and Seattle.  Excellent school district.  All of the commonly used stores such as Target, Trader Joe's and Costco are also conveniently located in town.  No freeway driving necessary.
whatownerloves: House has a treehouse feel from the kitchen and family room with views of the surrounding mountains and majestic trees.  Kitchen conveniently located between family room/breakfast bar and the formal dining and living room.  Living and family room both have large brick fireplaces.  Downstairs has access from garage and driveway directly into tiled mudroom for muddy/wet kids and pets.   Large fenced backyard for kids and dogs to run and play.  Separate laundry room with plenty of storage. Laundry chute from upstairs to laundry room.   Basement room for loud, musical kids.  Terrific, kind and quiet neighbors on ALL sides.  Lots of outdoor activities with plenty of designated hiking trails and Lake Samammish close by.  Snoqualmie skiing/boarding 30 minutes east.  School bus route for for all grades directly across the street.   Great community center with lots of activities for kids and adults (such as an indoor walking track) located in downtown.  Also indoor pool open year-round for lessons and recreation.  Downtown has wonderful restaurants and artists studios.  Salmon Festival every year in October hosts lots of food, incredible artists and performances.  Local theater group (Village Theater) hosts musicals and plays.  There is also Kidstage, a kids theater which has classes and performances.  A wonderful music store which offers lessons for all ages in almost every instrument.   Neighborhood has all ages from very small children to teens and retirees.  Dogs are a very welcome addition in this neighborhood.

homedescription:
This parcel is a rectangular parcel of 3,450 SF that is zoned L3. This Seattle zoning designation allows higher density and utility than most of the single family residential zoning found on Queen Anne Hill. The L3 zoning allows 3 story lowrise apartment buildings or townhome utility, with a 1/800 density indicator (12 units per 9,600 SF - 4 units on this parcel).
Maximum lot coverage is 45% (50% for townhomes) and up to 65% lot coverage. 
This residence could be remodeled as a 3 story home of much larger square footage on each level, or razed for the construction of up to 4 townhomes.
The property's immediate neighbor to the east - 922 Nob Hill - with similar view sold for almost $2.2
million in December, 2007.

Neighborhood Description

The property is located in the south Queen Anne Hill neighborhood blocks north of the Seattle Center and the downtown Seattle
city core. This hillside neighborhood is primarily older established homes (suburban utility with immediate urban amenities),
most of which have been fully renovated and/or upgraded. Due to the zoning along the southern rim of this neighborhood,
many of the older structures are being razed for new townhome or higher density construction. There are multiunit dwelling
opportunities along the periphery, as well as commercial and retail/entertainment opportunities. Due to the south sloping
hillside location, the predominant number of homes have varying degrees and quality of view amenity of the Seattle Center
(Space Needle), the city skyline, Lake Union or Elliot Bay, potential mountain range views to the east (Cascades) and west
(Olympics), and Mt Rainier (largest mountain in continental US).This property has convenient access to community support
services, shopping, restaurants, public schools, and city amenities and entertainment, all of which are within a 1/2 mile
radius. Access to arterials and freeways. Market appeal for the subject area is very good.

Life as a work of art - IN a work of art

Among the most desirable slices of heaven on Queen Anne.

This is a fully remodeled and updated home of quality construction and finish grade with a detached studio/yoga room of similar finish and view quality on the western portion of the parcel. It was a full remodel with new windows to of varying shapes to enhance the immediate view of the Space Needle to the south and the Seattle downtown skyline, new roofing, newer furnace and hotwater systems, all new extensive exterior surround-decking, and full kitchen remodel. Quality materials were utilized throughout carrying a similar wood theme; brazilian walnut ipe hardwood flooring on both levels, wenge hardwood kitchen counters and bath counters, custom hickory cabinetry and new quality appliances, all new solid core doors with an imported solid wood property entry door to the property from Bali, custom lighting and accent lighting, etc.
The home is laid out to maximize the very good Seattle view from both levels and the surrounding deck with glass railings enhances view from the entire length of the property (from yoga room in the west to the open deck hot tub layout to the east).
The property is partially enclosed to the north in bamboo hedges and the western portion is very well designed and landscaped with stone patio, water features, carved wood benches & planters, etc (See photos). Although the home has the potential for significant expansion, both vertically and horizontally, it will continue to compete well in the surrounding market place due to its quality, layout, view amenity, and very good location (Immediately proximate to the Seattle Center and on a dead-end road with no traffic influence). The quality of remodel and upgrading contribute to its effective age of 5 years

This home was built new in 2005 and is located in an upscale family oriented neighborhood only 10 minutes from downtown Seattle and within walking distance of Discovery Park and Magnolia Village.   This house has all of the features you would expect to find in a high-end home of this caliber.  The main floor has a Gourmet kitchen with high-end Sub Zero and Viking appliances, Brazilian cherry hardwood floors, spacious open light filled rooms with 10ft ceilings, crown moldings, slab granite countertops, custom cabinetry, gas log fireplaces, flat screen TV's, security system with cameras and much more.  Upstairs has a gorgeous master suite with two jack & Jill bedrooms and a oversize laundry/craft room.   The master suite has a walk in closet, jetted tub, oversize double shower, Onyx slab vanity top with heated granite floors and a large view deck.  The basement/garage is a car collectors dream come true.  With it's 10ft ceilings and 1740 square feet of fully finished wide open room, there is enough space to park up to ten cars!  Or if you're not into cars, there are plans in place to build out two large bedrooms with a huge media room.  (build out available upon request)    Superior craftsmanship and attention to detail is evident throughout this magnificent home.  Offered at $ 1,980,000.
whatownerloves: We love the quality of construction and the attention to detail that is evident throughout this beautiful home.  High end finishes and top of the line appliances are a definite bonus.  We spend a lot of time in the master suite.  Its spacious, yet cozy with all the amenities you could imagine.  The views of the sound and mountains are breath taking.  It's not unusual to see a giant cruise ship or aircraft carrier cruise bye.  We love the location, only 10 minutes from downtown and a short walk to Discovery park or Magnolia Village.  It feels like we're in the suburbs with all of the Large lots and  wide streets.  We love the garage!  We're car people and It houses all of our vehicles with room to spare.  And If we get tired of cars, we   planed ahead and have blueprints in place to convert the garage into more living space.  Easy deal.  In short, we love the layout, the finishes, the views, the neighborhood and the proximity to downtown Seattle.   You won't find a nicer neighborhood in the city of Seattle.

homedescription: Paradise presents itself on prestigious yet private Perkins Lane. Grand formal living & dining rooms flow to the sunroom all basking in warm southern views and highlighted by hardwood floors, cove ceilings, classic millwork and a period fireplace with marble surround. The kitchen is generous in size, designed with functionality in mind and offers excellent counter & cupboard space w/island breakfast bar, updated appliance package, wood burning stove, desk area and access to the rear patio & artists studio with 3/4 bath. The upper floor offers two spacious view bedrooms serviced by a full bath accented in travertine stone and a cozy water closet. The bedrooms enjoy access through French doors to the expansive deck terrace. Garage access is also located on this floor. Finished lower level offers rec/media room with stone fireplace & sunroom, two bedrooms serviced by a 3/4 bath and access to three large storage areas and the beach. If your interests involve boating, fishing, crabbing, beachcombing, camp fires and watching beavers, otters, salmon, whales & eagles this home offers a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity that must not be missed! homedescription:
This three bedroom, two bath is one of the few of the larger floor plans in Sixty 01 Village, a secure and gated complex that prides itself in providing residents with a myriad of amenities including but not limited to swimming pools, tennis and volleyball courts, a fitness center, a fully equipped clubhouse that can be reserved for special occasions, a cluster of beautiful picnic and BBQ locations, miles of private pathways adorned with well maintained flora, and three serene lakes filled with carp, sunfish, and a family of ducks. 

The entry of the condo is characterized by a set of double doors, perfect for transporting larger pieces of furniture in and out. Polished hardwood floors line the entryway and extend to the corridor, kitchen, and dining room. An assortment of quaint features such as a lazy Susan in one of the kitchen cupboards, track lighting in the bedroom and living room, and full length mirrors on all the bedroom closet doors add a level of uniqueness and distinguishment to the home. The living room, master bedroom, and one of the auxiliary rooms are all connected to private balconies. Each room enjoys spaciousness and ceiling to floor windows which further integrate the condo into the natural beauty directly outside. Speaking of natural beauty, the dozens of trees which surround the unit not only contribute to the seclusion and privacy of the condo, but also keep the interior cool even on Seattle's hottest days. With a walk-in closet in the master, another in the living room, as well as a storage unit in the building lobby provided by Sixty 01 alongside two covered parking spaces, storage is not likely to be an issue.
whatownerloves: The location, right in the heart of Bridle Trails, is perfection. A bus stop sits directly at the entrance of Sixty 01, just a few minutes walk away from this particular unit. This provides for an exceptionally easy and stress free commute to Microsoft, or even farther to Seattle Downtown or the UW. A few blocks down the street is a small shopping complex which includes a grocery store, drug store, and Starbucks.

homedescription:
Modern, cozy and private 2 bed/2 bath top floor - end unit condo - 900 sqft conveniently located near Redmond Town Center and Microsoft Campus. Luxury finishes include granite slab counters, modern wood cabinets, subway tile backsplash, and stainless steel GE appliances in kitchen, full W/D, premium bamboo hardwood flooring through out entire home including bedrooms, nice use of premium tiles, modern real-wood cabinets and chrome accents in bathrooms including elongated toilets, and 2 reserved parking spaces right outside your home, along with generous guest parking.

The feel of this home and community is best described similar to like staying at a modern lodge in Whistler Village, B.C. It's beautiful in the summer and cozy in the winter. This home is conveniently located on the east side central to a 5-10 minute drive time to downtown Bellevue, Kirkland Waterfront, and Woodinville (Wine Valley). Includes a community lodge with gym, media/event room, kitchenette, and outdoor patio with gas BBQ grill and an inviting fire pit.


Some Highlights:

* Modern architectural style and luxury finishes
* Top floor corner/end unit (3rd Floor) - with vaulted ceilings
* Surrounded by both broadleaf and pine trees providing beautiful year round nature views and virtually 100% privacy from other neighbors
* Daily sunrise drenches into the living room and master bedroom. Lot of natural light in all rooms
* Beautiful vaulted ceilings, wood burning fireplace, outside deck, and insulated double pane windows
* Includes double cell window shades for insulation and additional privacy
* Premium bamboo hardwood flooring throughout entire home including both bedrooms (no carpet)
* Spice pantry installed in kitchen and built-in kitchen bar counter open to living room
* Bedrooms are separate from each other and do not share a wall
* Nobody above you and only one small shared wall with the only other neighbor on top floor
* Master bath in master bedroom. Luxury elongated toilets
* Wired for tv cable in all rooms
* 2 dedicated parking spaces right out side home
* Attached storage closet outside by deck
* Water/Sewer/Garbage included in HOA dues
* 2-3 minutes away from 520 on-ramp and bus line to downtown Seattle.
* Minutes away from Woodinville (Wine Country), Kirkland Waterfront, Downtown Bellevue/Bellevue Square, Redmond Town Center, Marymoor Park & Dog Park, Lake Sammamish, Burke Gilman Trail, and more!

For a private showing appointment, please contact me via Zillow.
whatownerloves:
Corner top floor unit with 6 out of the 7 windows all featuring beautiful views of trees creating natural privacy without needing to use the blinds. Feels like a cozy winter lodge in the winter when snow has fallen covering the trees. Absolutely beautiful!

The morning sunrise and sunset light gushing into the home due to the unit being in the corner and on the top floor at same level as the tip top of the trees.

Both the master and guest bedrooms have been upgraded with the same beautiful bamboo hardwood floors.

Vaulted ceilings in the living room allows for taller bookshelves giving it a grander airier feel than lower units.

Great walkability to shopping, restaurants, Redmond Town Center mall in downtown Redmond.

Gym with treadmill, elliptical, and free weights is a nice plus!

From the Kitchen, open access flows into the Great Room, Nook and Formal Dinning area... This main floor design is an Entertainer's DREAM!! homedescription: This Burnstead home is located in the desirable Brighton Place on Education Hill. It offers all the conveniences of living in Redmond, with the serenity of the surrounding natural trail in front of the home and pond preserve in the back. Summers are spent entertaining on the back decks enjoying sunsets, hot air balloons in flight, croaking frogs and chirping birds.  The main floor includes the master with 2 piece bath, laundry room, powder room, formal living and dining areas, office, kitchen and family room. The basement has  three bedrooms with one large enough to serve as a second master, a full bath, living area, second office, media room, and craft or exercise room. The finished sub-basement acts as a 700 square foot accessory dwelling unit (mother-in-law) with separate entrance, 3/4 bath, one bedroom, washer/dryer and kitchen furnished in stainless appliances, granite and travertine finishes.  The garage houses 3 vehicles and enough storage for all the tools as well as a shop area. The home is equipped with two security systems, in-wall speaker system, 3-car garage and leaf guard gutters.

homedescription: One-of-a-Kind secluded one level home on 2.5 acres in East Redmond. Property has park-like grounds with several water features and many bearing fruit trees (apple, pear, pie cherries). Two-car attached garage as well as a separate large three-car/shop building with separate electrical billing for possible business use. Fenced in garden area to keep out deer and rabbits. A cottage-like garden house that could be used as a playhouse as well. A sizeable woodshed is nestled at the edge of the woods to support your unique Russian fireplace (requires less wood). Central vacuum, air conditioning, electronic air cleaner. Super large kitchen with solid oak cabinets, subzero refrigerator and freezer, two new skylights, granite island, peninsula, open to large family room with beautiful sunroom wall, fireplace and newly refinished hardwood flooring. Vaulted ceilings throughout most of the house. Step-down living room enclosed with a single and a double-French leaded-glass door for possible use as media room. Built in counter/cabinetry on one wall. The master bedroom opens out onto a concrete aggregate patio with an overhead wisteria-covered arbor leading to a covered gazebo with ironwood deck. A short curved sidewalk leads to another large covered deck off the family room with hot tub and natural gas barbecue. Master bathroom also features a glass-enclosed shower and large corner spa tub (no jets), and double sinks (one sink larger with shampoo sprayer). Master bedroom has his and her walk-in closets and high ceilings. Will consider selling master bedroom custom furniture with home. A second large bedroom has a nice walk in shampoo sink area and walk-in closet and exterior access onto a small patio. Third bedroom has walk-in closet as well. Very large laundry room with large sink, accessible from garage as mudroom. RV parking with nearby RV electrical hookup. New furnace in last 3 years, brand new roof last year with 25 year guarantee and all sunroom windows replaced last year. Home is in the sought-after Lake Washington school district.
whatownerloves: Quiet secluded privacy and connection with nature as if stepping into a different world.  Ideal for entertainment with the large covered hot tub deck area with natural gas barbecue.  The one level design also makes it ideal for retirement couples.  A back bedroom with adjoining bathroom can be blocked off for a mother-in-law suite as it has its own sliding glass door entrance onto a small patio.  A kitchen with enough cabinetry and space for a couple to both cook to their heart's desire without interfering with each other.  The kitchen open to the family room allows guests to socialize with the chefs as well.  Green Beauty out every window.

homedescription:
Located next to Idylwood Park Beach. 2 bedroom/ 2 bathrooms 1100+ Sq ft Condo. Carport. Freshest Air and Tastiest Water on tap. Relatively ordinary interior with some nice touches.  Walking distance to Microsoft. Kitchen, dining, living area with some Lake View.   Next to jog, bike paths and bus stand.  The city maintains your lovely backyard/ beach and only asks that you share it with a few people (a lot during summer time). 

Neighborhood Description

Beautiful scenic ("Viewpoint") neighborhood!  Take 520 here get off on NE 40th, walk around Idylwood park, drive along West Lake Sammamish and to the Shops at Redmond Center.  Drive around Marymoor Park. Cirque du Soleil, films and concerts play at Marymoor. This is one of the most affordable homes available in a top neighborhood thanks to ancient management problems--however anthropologists have cleared away the cavemen/women/saber-tooths.  2 New Medical clinics opened in the city.  Drive around it looks like a well-managed city! Courteous neighbors and drivers on the road.  Microsoft is one of 4 companies in the USA to have 'AAA' rating---higher than the U.S Govt!  This area has been a treasure in good times and a haven in the bad.  Commute to Amazon, Nintendo wii, Starbucks, Costco, even Zillow, big orders at Boeing, small medical companies. This part of the country is getting hotter...don't wait too long.
whatownerloves: Lots!  Drive around this area and experience it for yourself. Fast and Scenic (snow-capped mtns) commutes on the Eastside (Big Deal here). and moderate Summers, Serene Winters, sports in Spring and Fall.  Quiet and Peaceful.  Clean air and water on tap. Close to Marymoor Park with its tennis courts, baseball and soccer fields. Watch the rowing team on the lake.  Walking up the hill on NE40th is good exercise.  Idylwood Beach Parking is never a problem if you live here (carport parking). Great value!  Great as first home: accomodates some expansion, low maintenance, stable or growing area businesses.  Idylwood beach has a sandy not rocky beach...tan comfortably in your sand castle.

homedescription:
*This is a warm home that is the best in the development as it was completely remodeled right after taking possession of it as a brand new home!  Remodeling costs ran $40K on materials and stainless steel appliances.  The work was overseen and /or completed by myself except for tile work in the shower and master bath floor.
*This home comes with a very-well funded HOA reserve of over $500K (for 48 units) that covers everything for the next 20+ years except for utilities (including water/sewer), insurance, and landscaping which is covered by HOA dues of $310 month.
* Travel time to downtown Seattle is only 30 minutes.
* Hardwood maple cabinets in kitchen, 3 bathrooms, 4 in laundry room, and 4 in walk-in closet.  
* Maple laminate flooring in kitchen, downstairs bath, dining room, and entry.  
* Built in Queen "Murphy" bed in guest room.
* Exterior repainted in 2013 and interior in 2014.   
* Condo has a private back patio area for entertaining.    
* This unit has a large walk-in, tiled shower for two with 2 shower heads.
* The garage has two fold down/up 8ft work tables, 5 wall cabinets, and over 100 feet of shelving.
* Garage is fully insulated.
* Crown molding in the great room and master bed and bath rooms.
* Doggie door to the fenced back yard.
* All construction steps were inspected throughout by me and all work was done correctly.  I did most of the remodeling.
* Great room includes kitchen, dining, living, and area that can be used for office or formal dining.
* I am willing to guarantee everything including appliances for one year.      
* The taxes next year 2016 will be figured on $386K recent.
assessed value up $42K in one year.
* The unit would accommodate a fold down "lift" to the second floor from the entry way with minor renovation in case you or I needed it.
whatownerloves:
* The Great Room - Living, dining, kitchen, office.
* Lots of storage under stairs and in garage.
* Laundry room w/sink, washer, dryer, and maple cabinets.
* Stainless gas range, fridge, sink, BBQ, and dish washer.
* There is FREE access to many sports courts including: basketball, volleyball, tennis courts, soccer fields, and many other amenities like: parks and playgrounds is included in our master development agreement. 
* A golf course (Trilogy) is two blocks away.  
* A gym is three blocks away.
* Local QFC Market (two blocks away), and six good places to eat are less than five blocks away.  Two are award winners. 
* Has a very-well funded HOA reserve adding $10K to this home value.
* Parking for four cars - two smaller cars in the garage and two in large cars front of garage.
* A lot of Wildlife. 
* A Green Belt to the back. 
* Instant Hot Water in kitchen.  
* Has a large newer stainless BBQ worth $1.5K.
* We have underground power all the way to the power sub station, so have been without power only 8 hours total in the last 9 years.

homedescription: Located in one of the best 55 & older mobile home parks on the Eastside, this bright and cheerful 2 bedroom mobile home is in terrific move-in condition! Washer, dryer & refrigerator are included. The floor plan is really nice with the large utility room conveniently in the back portion of the home. There's a free-standing gas stove in the large living room. Outside there's 2 storage sheds and a big covered deck. This terrific mobile home sits on an extra large corner lot and it is low maintenance. Friendly Village Mobile Home Park is a wonderful place to live. There's a community swimming pool, scenic areas to stroll or have a picnic. The community clubhouse has 2 pool tables, a kitchen, an exercise room, laundry room, and more! The park has planned activities at the clubhouse and bus trips too. People living here have the privacy of having their own mobile home & when they want to socialize they just have to go on a stroll to meet up with very friendly, kind neighbors.

homedescription: Fabulous opportunity to own a custom built 3 bedroom 2.5 bath and den/office in Redmond on a horse acre of land with  breath taking views of the Cascade Mountains.  This home has been meticulously updated with hardwood floors throughout the lower level, Chef's kitchen with stainless steel appliances Miele double ovens, Bosche dishwasher and 6 burner stove. Custom cabinets with pull out drawers, lazy susans, hidden power strips and switches.  Built in microwave,  warming drawer and walk-in pantry.  Dining and family room each have French doors that open up to entertainment sized patio capturing the amazing views along with cabana/bar area along with hot tub and peaceful fish pond. In the evening, retreat into your master bedroom with its private balcony, fireplace and spa like bathroom featuring its own rain shower and jetted tub. Additional bedrooms are of ample size and one comes with a built in Murphy bed.  Additional house features include a built in bar in family room with lighted sink, built in speakers in family room, built in custom desk and book shelves in office and designer  light fixtures in dining and kitchen eating area.  Property also includes sprinkler system, 2 ponds, and wired 12x32 shop. And then there is the VIEW.  All  within minutes to Redmond, Fall City and Snoqualmie Falls. Close to the Bear Creek School and horse riding school. Private neighborhood for riding horses.  For more information please contact Yvette Hobzek at (206) 898-6859

Sophisticated elegance. Leland Place is a boutique condo development in the West of Market neighborhood of Kirkland. The building is concrete and steel construction for ultimate insulation and quiet quality. The unit includes AC as well.Pedini Italian cabinets highlight the designer kitchen. The home is private, beautiful, and has a large open living space. There is a very large 75 square foot walk-in closet. The bedroom is very spacious and large enough for a king bed and lounge chair / reading corner. The bathroom is spa quality and beautiful with travertine floor and shower and granite counter. Perhaps the largest and best 1-bedroom condo for rent in Kirkland.Parking in a secure garage is included. A large approx. 8' x 5' secured storage unit is also included.Utilities included in rent are water, sewage, and garbage. Tenant only pays the PSE and cable bill. Approximate monthly PSE gas and electric bill is $40-60 depending on heat / AC use.The building is very quiet and 5 minutes walk to downtown Kirkland. Heritage Park is just a block away as is the Kirkland waterfront. 

The condo is currently rented long term and not available for rental.

If you are inquiring about interest regarding purchasing this condo, please contact the seller via the Make Me Move form.
